-- Sun Capital Gets 190 Million Euros of Scotch & Soda LBO Loans
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 2012-02-09T14:31:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/sun-capital-gets-190-million-euros-of-scotch-soda-lbo-loans.html
Sun Capital Partners Inc. got 190
million euros ($252 million) of leveraged loans for its buyout
of Amsterdam-based apparel retailer Scotch & Soda.  ABN Amro Bank NV, Friesland Bank NV, ING Groep NV, IKB
Deutsche Industriebank AG, NIBC Holding NV, and Rabobank
International arranged the financing that includes term loans
and a revolving credit facility, lenders said in a statement
today.  An affiliate of  Boca Raton , Florida-based Sun Capital and
 Kellwood Co. (KWD)  said in July that it agreed to buy Scotch & Soda
for an undisclosed sum.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in London at 
